function (struct OverlayV1PricePoint.PricePoint storage ref[] storage pointer,struct OverlayV1PricePoint.PricePoint storage ref)

function (uint32[] memory) view external returns (int56[] memory,uint160[] memory)

computeDepth(uint256,uint256).details: Derived from cnstant product formula X*Y=K and tailored  to Uniswap V3 selective liquidity provision.

params._marketLiquidity: Amount of liquidity in market in ETH terms.

returns.depth_: Depth criteria for market in OVL terms.

depth().details: Returns the time weighted liquidity of the market feed in OVL terms at the current block.
depth().notice: The depth of the market feed in OVL terms at the current block.

returns.depth_: The time weighted liquidity in OVL terms.

enterOI(bool,uint256,uint256).details: This is invoked by Overlay collateral manager contracts, which can be for OVL, ERC20's, Overlay positions, NFTs, or what have you. The calculations for impact and fees are performed here.
enterOI(bool,uint256,uint256).notice: Adds open interest to the market

params._collateral: The amount of collateral in OVL terms to take the position out with.
params._isLong: The side of the market to enter open interest on.
params._leverage: The leverage with which to take out the position.

returns.collateralAdjusted_: Amount of collateral after impact and fees.
returns.debtAdjusted_: Amount of debt after impact and fees.
returns.fee_: The protocol fee to be taken.
returns.impact_: The market impact for the build.
returns.oiAdjusted_: Amount of open interest after impact and fees.
returns.pricePointNext_: The index of the price point for the position.

epochs(uint256,uint256).details: This returns the number of compoundings that have passed since the last time funding was paid as well as the timestamp of the current compounding epoch, which come at regular intervals according to the compounding period.
epochs(uint256,uint256).notice: The compounding information for computing funding.

params._now: The timestamp of the current block.

returns.compoundings_: The number of compounding periods passed since the last time funding was compounded.

exitData(bool,uint256).details: This is called by the collateral managers to retrieve the necessary information to calculate the specifics of each position, for instance the PnL or if it is liquidatable.
exitData(bool,uint256).notice: First part of the flow to remove OI from the system

params._isLong: Whether the data is being retrieved for a long or short.
params._pricePoint: Index of the initial price point
params.oiShares_: Total outstanding open interest shares on that side.
params.oi_: Total outstanding open interest on that side of the market.
params.priceFrame_: The price multiple comprised of the entry and exit prices for the position, with the exit price being the current one. Longs receive the bid on exit and the ask on entry shorts the opposite.

exitOI(bool,uint256,uint256,uint256,uint.details: Called as the second part of exiting oi, this function reports the open interest in OVL terms to remove as well as  open interest shares to remove. It also registers printing or burning of OVL in the process.
exitOI(bool,uint256,uint256,uint256,uint.notice: Removes open interest from the market

params._antiBrrrr: How much was burnt on closing the position.
params._brrrr: How much was printed on closing the position.
params._isLong: The side from which to remove open interest.
params._oi: The open interest to remove in OVL terms.
params._oiShares: The open interest shares to remove.

fetchPricePoint().details: Reads price and depth of market feed
fetchPricePoint().notice: Reads the current price and depth information

oi().details: Returns all up to date open interest data for the market.
oi().notice: The current open interest on both sides of the market.

returns.oiLongShares_: Current open interest shares on the long side.
returns.oiLong_: Current open interest on long side.
returns.oiShortShares_: Current open interest shares on the short side.
returns.oiShort_: Current open interest on short side.

oiCap().details: Returns the open interest cap for the market.
oiCap().notice: The open interest cap for the market

oiLong().notice: The current open interest on the long side.

returns.oiLong_: The current open interest on the long side.

oiShort().notice: The current open interest on the short side.

returns.oiShort_: The current open interest on the short side.

positionInfo(bool,uint256).details: These values are required to feed to the position calculations.
positionInfo(bool,uint256).notice: Exposes important info for calculating position metrics.

params._isLong: Whether position is on short or long side of market.

returns.oiShares_: The current open interest shares on the chosen side.
returns.oi_: The current open interest on the chosen side.
returns.priceFrame_: Price frame resulting from e entry and exit prices.

pricePointCurrent().details: Returns the price point if it exists.

pricePointNextIndex().details: Returns the index of the _next_ price
pricePointNextIndex().notice: Get the index of the next price to be realized

returns.nextIndex_: The length of the price point array

pricePoints(uint256).details: Returns the price point if it exists.

params._pricePointIndex: Index of the price point being queried.

update().details: This function updates the market with the latest price and conditionally reads the depth of the market feed. The market needs an update on the first call of any block.
update().notice: Internal update function to price, cap, and pay funding.

returns.cap_: The open interest cap for the market.
